article.headline: Texas-Arlington 68, Louisiana Tech 61
article.story: ARLINGTON, Texas -- Kevin Butler had 17 points and Bo Ingram added 11 as Texas-Arlington defeated Louisiana Tech 68-61 on Saturday night. Jordan Reves had eight points and 13 rebounds for the Mavericks (2-0). Trevor Gaskins led the Bulldogs (1-1) with 22 points and seven rebounds, and Cordarius Johnson added 11 points. Butler's two free throws gave Texas-Arlington a 47-46 lead with 9:03 remaining. Then, Ingram's 3-pointer ignited a 12-3 run over a span of 3:18 that gave the mavericks a 59-49 lead with just under six minutes to play. Texas-Arlington joins Louisiana Tech in the Western Athletic Conference next year.
